{"title_page": "Robert B. Spencer", "text_new": "{{short description|American far-right author and blogger}}\n{{other people|Robert Spencer}}\n{{distinguish|text=the white supremacist author and speaker [[Richard B. Spencer]]}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{pp-semi-blp|small=yes}}\n{{Infobox person <!--please see talk page re. choice of infobox format-->\n| name               = Robert Spencer\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              = Robert Spencer.jpg\n| image_size         = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = \n| monuments          = \n| nationality        = American\n| other_names        = \n| ethnicity          = \n| citizenship        = \n| alma_mater         = [[University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill]], (M.A. 1986, [[Religious Studies]])\n| occupation         = Author, blogger\n| years_active       = 2002\u2013present\n| employer           = \n| organization       = [[David Horowitz Freedom Center]]\n| agent              = \n| known_for          = [[Islamophobia|Anti-Muslim views]], <br />books and websites about <br />[[Jihad]] and [[Islamic terrorism]]\n| notable_works      = ''[[The Truth About Muhammad|The Truth About Muhammad: Founder of the World's Most Intolerant Religion]]'', (2006)<br />''[[The Politically Incorrect Guide to Islam (And the Crusades)]]'', (2005)\n| influences         = \n| influenced         = \n| home_town          = \n| salary             = \n| net_worth          = \n| television         = \n| party              = \n| movement           = \n| boards             = \n| religion           = \n| spouse             = \n| parents            = \n| relatives          = \n| awards             = \n| website            = {{URL|jihadwatch.org}}\n| footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Robert Bruce Spencer''' is an American anti-Muslim<ref name=\"Anti-Muslim-speakers-Washingtonpost\"/><ref name=\"Isaacs-Unz-American-Islamophobia\">{{cite web |last1=Isaacs |first1=Arnold |title=American Islamophobia's Fake Facts |url=http://www.unz.com/tengelhardt/american-islamophobias-fake-facts/ |website=The Unz Review |accessdate=July 13, 2019 |date=July 31, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Ernst-book-Islamophobia-in-America\">{{Cite book|url=https://www.palgrave.com/gp/book/9781137290069|title=Islamophobia in America - The Anatomy of Intolerance {{!}} C. Ernst {{!}} Palgrave Macmillan|last=|first=|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=4, 125-126, 163|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"BBC-US-bloggers-banned-from-UK\"/> author and [[blogger]]. Spencer describes himself as \"the 'good' kind of [[Islamophobia|Islamophobe]]\".<ref name=\"case-for-islamophobia-Spencer-frontpagemag\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.frontpagemag.com/fpm/268634/case-islamophobia-robert-spencer|title=The Case for Islamophobia|date=December 6, 2017|work=Frontpage Mag|access-date=May 23, 2018}}</ref> His published books include two [[New York Times Best Seller list|''New York Times'' bestsellers]].\n\nIn 2003 he founded and has since directed  [[Islamophobia|Islamophobe]] blog [[Jihad Watch]]. He co-founded the anti-Muslim group [[Stop Islamization of America]] (American Freedom Defense Initiative) with blogger [[Pamela Geller]].<ref name=\"KaplanL\u00f6\u00f6w2017\">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mxE4DwAAQBAJ&pg=PT214|title=Lone Wolf and Autonomous Cell Terrorism|author1=Jeffrey Kaplan|author2=Hel\u00e9ne L\u00f6\u00f6w|author3=Leena Malkki|publisher=Taylor & Francis|year=2017|isbn=978-1-317-53042-8|page=214}}</ref> Reports that two of Spencer's books were listed in [[FBI]] training materials and that he had given seminars to various law enforcement units in the United States stirred controversy.<ref name=\"Anti-Muslim-speakers-Washingtonpost\">{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/religion/anti-muslim-speakers-still-popular-in-law-enforcement-training/2014/03/12/bc8d8e30-aa1c-11e3-8a7b-c1c684e2671f_story.html|title=Anti-Muslim speakers still popular in law enforcement training|date=March 12, 2014|work=[[The Washington Post]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170318114828/https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/religion/anti-muslim-speakers-still-popular-in-law-enforcement-training/2014/03/12/bc8d8e30-aa1c-11e3-8a7b-c1c684e2671f_story.html|archive-date=March 18, 2017|url-status=live|access-date=September 10, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" /> He has frequently appeared on [[Fox News]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mediamatters.org/blog/2015/01/13/meet-the-extremists-who-lead-foxs-conversation/202119|title=Meet The Extremists Who Lead Fox's Conversation About Islam|date=January 13, 2015|work=[[Media Matters]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170211080539/https://mediamatters.org/blog/2015/01/13/meet-the-extremists-who-lead-foxs-conversation/202119|archive-date=February 11, 2017|url-status=live|access-date=February 10, 2017}}</ref>  In 2013 the [[UK Home Office]] barred Spencer from travel to the [[UK]] for 3 to 5 years for \"making [[#uk ban statement|statements]]  that may foster hatred that might lead to inter-community violence\".\n\n==Background==\nSpencer was baptized in the [[Greek Orthodox Church]] and joined the [[Melkite Greek Catholic Church]] in 1984.<ref name=\"Spencer bio\">{{cite web|url=http://www.jihadwatch.org/about-robert-spencer.html|title=About Robert Spencer|publisher=Jihad Watch|accessdate=October 29, 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101229102419/http://www.jihadwatch.org/about-robert-spencer.html|archivedate=December 29, 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"Spero News\">{{cite news|url=http://www.speroforum.com/a/42470/Pope-must-condemn-demonizing-of-Israel|title=Pope must condemn demonizing of Israel|last=Spencer|first=Robert|date=October 26, 2010|work=Spero News|access-date=October 29, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101029001117/http://www.speroforum.com/a/42470/Pope-must-condemn-demonizing-of-Israel|archive-date=October 29, 2010|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":3\" /> In a 2006 interview, Spencer stated that his grandparents were forced to emigrate from an area that is now part of Turkey because they were [[Christianity|Christians]].<ref name=\"lamb\">{{cite web|url=http://www.c-span.org/video/?193778-1/qa-robert-spencer|date=August 20, 2006|title=Robert Spencer Jihad Watch, Director Q & A with Brian Lamb|publisher=CSpan|accessdate=November 30, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141109043825/http://www.c-span.org/video/?193778-1%2Fqa-robert-spencer|archive-date=November 9, 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> According to a 2010 interview in ''[[New York (magazine)|New York]]'' magazine, Spencer's father worked for the [[Voice of America]] during the [[Cold War]], and in his younger days, Spencer himself worked at Revolution Books, a [[Maoist]] bookstore in [[New York City]] founded by [[Robert Avakian]].<ref name=\"Muhammad comes to\">{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/news/features/67635/index2.html|title=Muhammad Comes to Manhattan|work=New York|author=Mark Jacobson|date=August 22, 2010|accessdate=November 1, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100826065300/http://nymag.com/news/features/67635/index2.html|archive-date=August 26, 2010|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nSpencer received an M.A. in 1986 in [[religious studies]] from the [[University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill]]. His masters thesis was on Catholic history.<ref name=UNC>{{cite web|url=http://webcat.lib.unc.edu/record=b2172870~S1|publisher=UNC-CH Libraries|work=Davis Library Thesis, Religion, 1986|title=The monophysite in the mirror, by Robert Bruce Spencer|access-date=March 20, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170301144945/http://webcat.lib.unc.edu/record=b2172870~S1|archive-date=March 1, 2017|url-status=live|year=1986}}</ref> He has said he has been studying Islamic theology, law, and history since 1980.<ref name=\"lamb\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://trib.com/news/local/article_2428fa7c-c843-561b-80ac-b243218b92be.html |title=Marines gather to honor, celebrate |publisher=Trib.com |date=October 26, 2005 |accessdate=November 1, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170908021137/http://trib.com/news/local/article_2428fa7c-c843-561b-80ac-b243218b92be.html |archive-date=September 8, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> He worked in [[think tank]]s for more than 20 years,<ref name=\"Muhammad comes to\"/> and in 2002\u20132003 was an adjunct fellow with the [[Free Congress Research and Education Foundation|Free Congress Foundation]].<ref name=\"tribute\">{{cite web|url=http://www.catholic.org/national/national_story.php?id=31171|title=A Tribute: Paul Weyrich Has Died|date=December 19, 2008|accessdate=December 16, 2010|author=Robert Spencer|publisher=Catholic Online|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090309161405/http://www.catholic.org/national/national_story.php?id=31171|archivedate=March 9, 2009}}</ref> Spencer named [[Paul Weyrich]], also a Melkite Catholic, as a mentor of his writings on Islam. Spencer writes, \"Paul Weyrich taught me a great deal, by word and by example&nbsp;\u2013 about how to deal both personally and professionally with the slanders and smears that are a daily aspect of this work.\"<ref name=\"tribute\"/>\n\nCriticized by clergy in the Catholic Church because of his views on Islam, Spencer left the church in 2016 to return to the [[Greek Orthodox Church]].<ref name=\":3\">{{cite web|url=https://www.crisismagazine.com/2018/robert-spencer-and-the-religion-of-terror|title=Robert Spencer and the Religion of Terror|work=Crisis Magazine|author=Jeffrey Rubin|date=October 25, 2018|accessdate=October 26, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181025120653/https://www.crisismagazine.com/2018/robert-spencer-and-the-religion-of-terror|archive-date=October 25, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Views on Islam==\nSpencer is known for his anti-Muslim views.<ref name=\"Anti-Muslim-speakers-Washingtonpost\"/><ref name=\"Isaacs-Unz-American-Islamophobia\"/><ref name=\"Ernst-book-Islamophobia-in-America\"/><ref name=\"BBC-US-bloggers-banned-from-UK\"/><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomsbury.com/uk/right-wing-populism-in-europe-9781780932453/|title=Right-Wing Populism in Europe|website=Bloomsbury Publishing|pages=90\u201392|language=en|access-date=July 12, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/08/04/us/04extreme.html|title=To Fight Radical Islam, U.S. Wants Muslim Allies|last=Shane|first=Scott|date=August 3, 2011|work=The New York Times|access-date=April 21, 2019|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.desmoinesregister.com/story/news/politics/2017/01/29/iowas-congressional-delegation-responds-trump-immigration-order/97221888/|title=Iowa's congressional delegation responds to Trump immigration order|website=Des Moines Register|language=en|access-date=July 12, 2019}}</ref> Spencer describes himself a [[Islamophobe]] of \"Good kind\" ,<ref name=\"case-for-islamophobia-Spencer-frontpagemag\"/> and is a commentator on [[radical Islam]].<ref name=\"Deland 2014 p. 162\">{{cite book|title=In the Tracks of Breivik: Far Right Networks in Northern and Eastern Europe|last=Deland|first=Mats|publisher=Lit Verlag|year=2014|isbn=978-3-643-90542-0|location=Berlin Wien|page=162}}</ref>\n\nSpencer co-founded the anti-Muslim<ref name=\"Anti-Muslim-speakers-Washingtonpost\"/><ref name=\"Isaacs-Unz-American-Islamophobia\"/><ref name=\"Ernst-book-Islamophobia-in-America\"/><ref name=\"BBC-US-bloggers-banned-from-UK\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-23064355|title=US bloggers banned from entering UK|date=June 26, 2013|access-date=July 11, 2019|language=en-GB}}</ref> group [[Stop Islamization of America]] (also known as the [[American Freedom Defense Initiative]]) with [[Pamela Geller]] in 2010. The organization is designated as a [[hate group]] by the [[Anti-Defamation League]]<ref>[http://www.adl.org/main_Extremism/sioa.htm \"Backgrounder: Stop Islamization of America (SIOA)\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120502054200/http://www.adl.org/main_Extremism/sioa.htm |date=May 2, 2012 }}. ''Extremism''. [[Anti-Defamation League]]. March 25, 2011 [August 26, 2010]. Retrieved February 16, 2012.</ref> and the [[Southern Poverty Law Center]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Lach, Eric|date=March 1, 2011|work=[[Talking Points Memo]]|url=http://tpmmuckraker.talkingpointsmemo.com/2011/03/pam_geller_on_splc_hate_group_label_badge_of_honor.php|title=Pam Geller On 'Hate Group' Label: 'A Badge of Honor'|access-date=February 17, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120313082234/http://tpmmuckraker.talkingpointsmemo.com/2011/03/pam_geller_on_splc_hate_group_label_badge_of_honor.php|archive-date=March 13, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Pamela Geller & Stop Islamization of America|url=http://www.splcenter.org/get-informed/intelligence-files/profiles/pamela-geller|publisher=Southern Poverty Law Center|accessdate=June 27, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110625194540/http://www.splcenter.org/get-informed/intelligence-files/profiles/pamela-geller|archive-date=June 25, 2011|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Steinback|first=Robert|title=Jihad Against Islam|url=http://www.splcenter.org/get-informed/intelligence-report/browse-all-issues/2011/summer/jihad-against-islam|work=Intelligence Report, Issue #142|publisher=Southern Poverty Law Center|accessdate=June 27, 2011|date=Summer 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120119075935/http://www.splcenter.org/get-informed/intelligence-report/browse-all-issues/2011/summer/jihad-against-islam|archive-date=January 19, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> Along with Geller, he led a campaign to stop the building of Park51, an Islamic community center near the World Trade Center, which they referred to as the \"Ground Zero Mosque\".<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn 2009, Spencer said Obama was to blame for false rumors that he was a \"secret Muslim\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/06/03/muslim-again/|title=Muslim Again?|last=Etheridge|first=Eric|date=June 3, 2009|website=Opinionator|language=en-US|access-date=July 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2011, ''[[Wired (Magazine)|Wired]]'' reported that two of Spencer's books were listed in [[FBI]] training materials. Both ''[[The Truth About Muhammad]]'' and ''[[The Politically Incorrect Guide to Islam]]'' were recommended for agents hoping to better understand Islam.<ref name=\":1\">{{cite journal|author=Ackerman, Spencer|date=July 27, 2011|journal=[[Wired (Magazine)|Wired]]|url=https://www.wired.com/2011/07/fbi-islam-101-guide/|title=FBI 'Islam 101' Guide Depicted Muslims as 7th-Century Simpletons|access-date=November 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181204011823/https://www.wired.com/2011/07/fbi-islam-101-guide/|archive-date=December 4, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Anders Behring Breivik|Anders Breivik]], the Norwegian spree killer behind the [[2011 Norway attacks|2011 Norway terrorist attacks]] which killed 77, cited Spencer 64 times in his manifesto and wrote of him, \"About Islam I recommend essentially everything written by Robert Spencer.\"<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Gardell|first=Mattias|date=January 1, 2014|title=Crusader Dreams: Oslo 22/7, Islamophobia, and the Quest for a Monocultural Europe|journal=Terrorism and Political Violence|volume=26|issue=1|pages=129\u2013155|doi=10.1080/09546553.2014.849930|issn=0954-6553}}</ref> Spencer condemned Breivik and said he was unfairly blamed by the media for the attack.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/25/us/25debate.html|title=Killings in Norway Spotlight Anti-Muslim Thought in U.S.|last=Shane|first=Scott|date=July 24, 2011|work=The New York Times|access-date=July 12, 2019|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref name=\":2\" />\n\n==Controversies==\nThe government of Pakistan banned Spencer's book, ''[[The Truth About Muhammad]]'', in 2016, citing \"objectionable material\" as the cause.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.nationalreview.com/phi-beta-cons/45068/pakistan-book-closed-muhammad-candace-de-russy |title= Pakistan: Book Closed on Muhammad |access-date= April 19, 2015 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150612204845/http://www.nationalreview.com/phi-beta-cons/45068/pakistan-book-closed-muhammad-candace-de-russy |archive-date= June 12, 2015 |url-status= live |date= January 9, 2007 }}</ref> ''[[Onward Muslim Soldiers]]'' was banned in Malaysia in 2007.<ref name=\"BERNAMA\">{{cite news|title=Ministry Bans 14 Books|url=http://www.bernama.com.my/bernama/v3/printable.php?id=272915|newspaper=[[BERNAMA]]|date=July 12, 2007|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303221210/http://www.bernama.com.my/bernama/v3/printable.php?id=272915|archivedate=March 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn an October 2010 news article, an investigative report by ''[[The Tennessean]]'' described Spencer as one of several individuals who \"... cash in on spreading hate and fear about Islam.\" ''Tennessean'' investigation concluded: \"IRS filings from 2008 show that Robert Spencer earned $132,537 from the [[David Horowitz Freedom Center]], and Horowitz pocketed over $400,000 for himself in just one year.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tennessean.com/article/20101024/NEWS01/10240374/Anti-Muslim-crusaders-make-millions-spreading-fear|title=Anti-Muslim crusaders make millions spreading fear|date=October 24, 2010|accessdate=November 4, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tennessean.com/assets/pdf/DN1658821023.PDF|title=David Horowitz Freedom Center's IRS Form 990|date=June 3, 2009|accessdate=April 24, 2011}}</ref>\n\nOn April 13, 2017, Spencer spoke at the [[Truman State University]] despite protests and a petition against him. He was invited by the [[Young America's Foundation]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/education/truman-state-grapples-with-controversial-anti-muslim-speaker/article_138f0acd-bd84-59e1-890e-d921a1ec6ee2.html|title=Truman State grapples with controversial anti-Muslim speaker|publisher=St. Louis Post-Dispatch|access-date=May 3, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424121832/http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/education/truman-state-grapples-with-controversial-anti-muslim-speaker/article_138f0acd-bd84-59e1-890e-d921a1ec6ee2.html|archive-date=April 24, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On May 1, 2017, Spencer spoke at the [[University of Buffalo]]. There he was shouted down and heckled.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://buffalonews.com/2017/05/01/controversial-speaker-ub-shouted-heckled/|title=No violence, but UB speaker greeted with tension, heckling|publisher=The Buffalo News|access-date=May 3, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170502134727/http://buffalonews.com/2017/05/01/controversial-speaker-ub-shouted-heckled/|archive-date=May 2, 2017|url-status=live|date=May 2, 2017}}</ref> On May 3, 2017, Spencer spoke at [[Gettysburg College]]; 375 alumni urged the college president [[Janet Morgan Riggs]] to cancel the speech, but the event went on as planned.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://gettysburgian.com/2017/05/open-letter-from-375-alums-urges-president-riggs-to-cancel-robert-spencers-speech/|title=Open letter from 375 alums urges President Riggs to cancel Robert Spencer's speech|date=May 1, 2017|newspaper=[[The Gettysburgian]]|access-date=May 3, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170503155217/http://gettysburgian.com/2017/05/open-letter-from-375-alums-urges-president-riggs-to-cancel-robert-spencers-speech/|archive-date=May 3, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Spencer said, \"There is one kind of diversity that is not valued generally in an academic setting and that is intellectual diversity.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://gettysburgian.com/2017/05/robert-spencers-speech-at-gettysburg-college-engages-students-in-civil-discourse/|title=Robert Spencer's speech at Gettysburg College engages students in civil discourse|author=Pontz, Benjamin|date=May 3, 2017|newspaper=The Gettysburgian|access-date=May 4, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170504173030/http://gettysburgian.com/2017/05/robert-spencers-speech-at-gettysburg-college-engages-students-in-civil-discourse/|archive-date=May 4, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On November 14, 2017, Spencer spoke at [[Stanford University]]. Many students walked out during the event.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcbayarea.com/news/local/Stanford-Students-Walk-Out-Protest-During-Robert-Spencer-Speaking-Event-457635203.html|title=Stanford Students Walk Out, Protest During Robert Spencer Speaking Event|publisher=NBC Bay Area|access-date=November 16, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171117001808/https://www.nbcbayarea.com/news/local/Stanford-Students-Walk-Out-Protest-During-Robert-Spencer-Speaking-Event-457635203.html|archive-date=November 17, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nSpencer said that \"a young Icelandic Leftist\" poisoned him in 2017 in Reykjavik, Iceland.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://icelandmag.is/article/controversial-us-author-robert-spencer-claims-he-was-poisoned-leftist-while-iceland |title = Controversial US author Robert Spencer claims he was poisoned by \"leftist\" while in Iceland}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://grapevine.is/news/2017/05/16/islamophobe-robert-spencer-claims-young-leftist-poisoned-him/ |title = Islamophobe Robert Spencer Claims Young Leftist Poisoned Him|date = May 16, 2017}}</ref> Spencer also criticized the doctor who then treated him and the police who investigated.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://archives.frontpagemag.com/fpm/leftist-privilege-poisoned-iceland-year-ago-no-one-robert-spencer/ |title =Leftist Privilege: Poisoned in Iceland a year ago, no one arrested |publisher=[[Frontpagemag]] |date=May 21, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Ban from entering the UK===\nOn June 26, 2013, Spencer and [[Pamela Geller]] were banned from entering the UK.<ref>{{cite news|title=US bloggers banned from entering UK|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-23064355|accessdate=June 27, 2013|publisher=BBC|date=June 26, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130627011447/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-23064355|archive-date=June 27, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> They were due to speak at an [[English Defence League]] march in [[Woolwich]], south London, where Drummer [[Murder of Lee Rigby|Lee Rigby]] was killed. [[Home Secretary]] [[Theresa May]] informed Spencer and Geller that their presence in the UK would \"not be conducive to the public good\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Rawlinson|first=Kevin|title=Anti-Ground Zero Mosque campaigners Pamela Geller and Robert Spencer barred from entering Britain to speak at an EDL rally|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/antiground-zero-mosque-campaigners-pamela-geller-and-robert-spencer-barred-from-entering-britain-to-speak-at-an-edl-rally-8675251.html|accessdate=June 27, 2013|newspaper=The Independent|date=June 26, 2013|location=London|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130627192049/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/antiground-zero-mosque-campaigners-pamela-geller-and-robert-spencer-barred-from-entering-britain-to-speak-at-an-edl-rally-8675251.html|archive-date=June 27, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nA letter from the UK Home Office stated that this decision is based on Spencer's statement that: \"It [Islam] is a religion or a belief system that mandates warfare against unbelievers for the purpose of establishing a societal model that is absolutely incompatible with Western society. ...Because of media and general government unwillingness to face the sources of Islamic terrorism these things remain largely unknown.\"<ref>{{cite video|title=The Speech that Got Robert Spencer Banned From the UK|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=June 27, 2013|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rHdUgc6gxDI|access-date=December 1, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202053606/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rhdugc6gxdi|archive-date=February 2, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe decision<!-- \", which they cannot appeal,\"-it was appealed in 2015-see below--> will stand for between three and five years. The ban followed a concerted campaign by the UK anti-racism organization [[Hope not Hate]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Anti-Muslim pair banned from UK|url=http://www.express.co.uk/news/uk/410494/Anti-Muslim-pair-banned-from-UK|accessdate=June 27, 2013|newspaper=Daily Express|location=UK|date=June 26, 2013}}</ref> which said it had collected 26,000 signatures for a petition to the Home Secretary.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lowles|first=Nick|title=Geller and Spencer Banned|url=http://www.hopenothate.org.uk/blog/article/2803/geller-and-spencer-banned|publisher=Hope not Hate|accessdate=June 27, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130630023715/http://www.hopenothate.org.uk/blog/article/2803/geller-and-spencer-banned|archive-date=June 30, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> Spencer and Geller contested the ban, but in 2015 the [[British Court of Appeals]] dismissed the appeal, arguing  that \"this was a public order case where the police had advised that significant public disorder and serious violence might ensue from the proposed visit.\"<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bailii.org/cgi-bin/markup.cgi?doc=/ew/cases/EWCA/Civ/2015/45.html&query=geller&method=boolean | title=Geller & Anor, R (on the application of) v The Secretary of State for the Home Department [2015] EWCA Civ 45 (05 February 2015) | publisher=[[British and Irish Legal Information Institute]] | accessdate=October 31, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"UK Human Rights Blog\">{{cite web | url=https://ukhumanrightsblog.com/2015/02/15/critics-of-islam-prevented-from-entering-uk-to-attend-lee-rigby-rally/ | title=Critics of Islam prevented from entering UK to attend Lee Rigby rally | publisher=1 Crown Office Row | work=UK Human Rights Blog | date=February 15, 2015 | accessdate=October 31, 2017 | author=English, Rosalind}}</ref>\n\nThe ban was criticised by [[Douglas Murray (author)|Douglas Murray]]. He stated that Islamist hate preachers are still allowed to enter the UK.<ref>{{cite news|title=A gross double standard over hate speech|url=http://blogs.spectator.co.uk/2013/06/a-gross-double-standard-over-hate-speech/|accessdate=February 8, 2017|newspaper=[[The Spectator]]|location=UK|date=June 27, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114143645/http://blogs.spectator.co.uk/2013/06/a-gross-double-standard-over-hate-speech/|archive-date=November 14, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n\n===Best sellers===\n* ''[[The Truth About Muhammad: Founder of the World's Most Intolerant Religion]]'', [[Regnery Publishing|Regnery Press]], 2006 ([[New York Times|NYT]] bestseller list \u2013 2006-10-29<ref name=autogenerated1>[https://www.nytimes.com/2006/10/29/books/bestseller/1029besthardnonfiction.html?ex=1168923600&en=acb5c34abdb92f18&ei=5070 Best Sellers \u2013 Hardcover Nonfiction] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402190205/http://www.nytimes.com/2006/10/29/books/bestseller/1029besthardnonfiction.html?ex=1168923600&en=acb5c34abdb92f18&ei=5070 |date=April 2, 2015 }} \u2013 [[NYT]]</ref>) {{ISBN|1-59698-028-1}} {{OCLC|232648493}}\n* ''[[The Politically Incorrect Guide to Islam (And the Crusades)]]'', Regnery Press, 2005. (NYT bestseller list \u2013 2005-10-16<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2005/10/16/books/bestseller/1016bestpapernonfiction.html?ex=1168923600&en=f4feabaad368de1c&ei=5070 Paperback Nonfiction] \u2013 [[NYT]]</ref>) {{ISBN|0-89526-013-1}} {{OCLC|779057129}}\n\n===Other books===\n*{{cite book|title=Palestinian Delusion: The Catastrophic History of the Middle East Peace Process|publisher=Bombardier Book|date=December 3, 2019|isbn=978-1642932546|oclc=}}\n* {{cite book|title=The History of Jihad: From Muhammad to ISIS|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1682616606|publisher=Bombardier Books|date=August 7, 2018|isbn=9781682616598|oclc=1046676281}}\n* {{cite book|title=Confessions of an Islamophobe|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1682614913|publisher=Bombardier Books|date=November 28, 2017|isbn=978-1682614914|oclc=1022710774}}\n* {{cite book|title=Not Peace But a Sword: The Great Chasm Between Christianity and Islam|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1938983289|publisher=Catholic Answers|date=March 25, 2013|isbn=978-1938983283|oclc=840646024}}\n* {{cite book|title=The Post-American Presidency: The Obama Administration's War on America|author=Pamela Geller|author2=Robert Spencer |publisher=Threshold Editions|date=July 27, 2010|isbn=978-1-4391-8930-6|title-link=The Post-American Presidency: The Obama Administration's War on America}}\n* {{cite book|title=The Complete Infidel's Guide to Free Speech (and Its Enemies)|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1621576515|publisher= Regnery Press|date=July 24, 2017|page=256|isbn=978-1621576273|oclc=993696636}}\n* {{cite book|title=The Complete Infidels' Guide to Iran|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1621575306|publisher= Regnery Press|date=July 11, 2016|page=256|isbn=978-1621575160|oclc= \t952247204}}\n* {{cite book|title=The Complete Infidel's Guide to ISIS|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1621574644|publisher= Regnery Press|date=August 24, 2015|page=|isbn=978-1-62157-453-8|oclc= \t916923210}}\n* {{cite book|title=The Complete Infidels' Guide to the Koran|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1596981261|publisher= Regnery Press|date=September 21, 2009|page=260|isbn=978-1-59698-104-1|oclc=317454159}}\n** downloadable version<ref>{{cite web|url=https://issuu.com/guraja/docs/spencer__robert_-_the_complete_infi  |title=The Complete Infidels Guide to the Koran  |author=Spencer, Robert|date=September 21, 2009|work=[[Simon & Schuster]] |accessdate=March 9, 2020}}</ref>\n* {{cite book|title=Did Muhammad Exist?: An Inquiry Into Islam's Obscure Origins|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1497608562|publisher=ISI Books|date=March 2012|isbn=978-1-61017-061-1|oclc=883649585}}\n* {{cite book|title=Stealth Jihad: How Radical Islam is Subverting America without Guns or Bombs|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1596980753|publisher=Regnery Press|date=October 28, 2008|isbn=978-1-59698-556-8|oclc=740862521}}\n* {{cite book|title=Religion of Peace?: Why Christianity Is and Islam Isn't|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1596985356|publisher=Regnery Publishing|year=2007|page=|isbn=978-1-59698-515-5|oclc=929251820}}\n* ''[[The Myth of Islamic Tolerance|The Myth of Islamic Tolerance: How Islamic Law Treats Non-Muslims]]'' (editor), [[Prometheus Books]], 2005. {{ISBN|1-59102-249-5}} {{OCLC|551266709}}\n* ''[[Onward Muslim Soldiers|Onward Muslim Soldiers: How Jihad Still Threatens America and the West]]'', [[Regnery Publishing]], 2003. {{ISBN|0-89526-100-6}} {{OCLC|892799748}}\n* {{cite book|title=Inside Islam: A Guide for Catholics: 100 questions and answers|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=0965922855|publisher=Ascension Press|year=2003|page=197|isbn=978-0-9659228-5-2}}\n* {{cite book|title=Islam Unveiled: Disturbing Questions About the World's Fastest Growing Faith|url=https://archive.org/details/islamunveileddis00robe|url-access=registration|publisher=Encounter Books|date=October 25, 2002|page=[https://archive.org/details/islamunveileddis00robe/page/202 202]|isbn=978-1-893554-58-0|oclc=752326911}}\n** downloadable version<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=eanFm7hiM1cC&q=page+75#v=onepage&q=page%2075&f=false  |title=Islam Unveiled: Disturbing Questions about the World's Fastest-Growing Faith |author=Spencer, Robert|date=October 25, 2002|work=[[Encounter Books]]|accessdate=March 9, 2020|isbn=9781594032950 }}</ref>\n* {{cite book|title=The Arab Winter Comes to America: The Truth about the War We're In|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=S2pLngEACAAJ|date=April 14, 2014|publisher=Regnery Publishing, Incorporated, An Eagle Publishing Company|isbn=978-1-62157-204-6|oclc=877883931}}\n\n===Pamphlets===\n\n*{{Citation\n| last       = \n| first      =\n| year       = 2013\n| title      = Islam: Religion of Bigots\n| publisher  = The David Horowitz Freedom Center\n| location =\n| page       = 20\n| url        = http://www.frontpagemag.com/sites/default/files/uploads/2013/10/religionofbigots.pdf\n| asin       = B00EYQZS9Y\n}}\n*{{Citation\n| last       = \n| first      =\n| year       = 2011\n| title      = Islamophobia: Thought Crime of the Totalitarian Future\n| publisher  = The David Horowitz Freedom Center\n| location =\n| page       = 56\n| url        =\n| asin       = B005R3336I\n}}\n*{{Citation\n| last       = \n| first      =\n| year       = 2011\n| title      = Muslim Persecution of Christians\n| publisher  = The David Horowitz Freedom Center\n| location =\n| page       = 40\n| url        =\n| asin       = B0058P4PHG\n}}\n*{{Citation\n| last       = \n| first      =\n| year       = 2012\n| title      = Muslim Brotherhood in America\n| publisher  = The David Horowitz Freedom Center\n| location =\n| page       = 28\n| url        = http://www.frontpagemag.com/sites/default/files/uploads/2011/03/mbia.pdf\n| asin       = B007GEJD92\n}}\n*{{Citation\n| last       = \n| first      =\n| year       = 2007\n| title      = What Americans Need to Know About Jihad\n| publisher  = The David Horowitz Freedom Center\n| location =\n| page       = 15\n| url        = http://www.frontpagemag.com/sites/default/files/uploads/2011/03/jihad.pdf\n| asin       = B0058PIX74\n}}\n\n===Interviews===\n*{{YouTube|HcEUz0gPaUE|The Glenn Beck Podcast Ep. 2}} by [[Glenn Beck]]\n*{{YouTube|sma4WYRuTXY|Bill O'Reilly's Interview with Robert Spencer}} by [[Bill O'Reilly (political commentator)|Bill O'Reilly]]\n*[http://www1.cbn.com/content/robert-spencer-politically-incorrect-guide-islam Pat Robertson interview] by [[Pat Robertson]]\n*{{YouTube|D7zpH4xt5rA|THE SAAD TRUTH_174}} by [[Gad Saad]]\n*{{YouTube|qvjeRFQvbrY|Confessions of An Islamophobe}}\n\n==See also==\n{{Wikipedia books\n |1=Robert Spencer\n}}\n{{Portal|Islam|Freedom of speech}}\n* [[List of books banned by governments]]\n* [[A Common Word Between Us and You]]\n* [[Catholic\u2013Muslim Forum]]\n* ''[[Islam: What the West Needs to Know]]''\n* [[John Paul II Center for Interreligious Dialogue]]\n* [[Pontifical Council for Interreligious Dialogue]]\n* [[Bibliography of books critical of Islam]]\n* [http://www.worldcat.org/identities/lccn-n2002-104117/ WorldCat author entry for 'Spencer, Robert 1962-']\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* Robert Spencer's [http://jihadwatch.org/ weblog, ''jihadwatch'']\n*{{C-SPAN|Robert Spencer}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Spencer, Robert}}\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:American bloggers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American political writers]]\n[[Category:American male non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:American social commentators]]\n[[Category:Counter-jihad activists]]\n[[Category:American critics of Islam]]\n[[Category:Middle Eastern Christians]]\n[[Category:Opposition to Islam in the United States]]\n[[Category:University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill alumni]]\n[[Category:21st-century American non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:Converts to Eastern Catholicism from Eastern Orthodoxy]]\n[[Category:Converts to Eastern Orthodoxy from Catholicism]]\n[[Category:Greek Orthodox Christians from the United States]]\n[[Category:American male bloggers]]\n[[Category:Islamophobia in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American far-right author and blogger}}\n{{other people|Robert Spencer}}\n{{distinguish|text=the white supremacist author and speaker [[Richard B. Spencer]]}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{pp-semi-blp|small=yes}}\n{{Infobox person <!--please see talk page re. choice of infobox format-->\n| name               = Robert Spencer\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              = Robert Spencer.jpg\n| image_size         = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = \n| monuments          = \n| nationality        = American\n| other_names        = \n| ethnicity          = \n| citizenship        = \n| alma_mater         = [[University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill]], (M.A. 1986, [[Religious Studies]])\n| occupation         = Author, blogger\n| years_active       = 2002\u2013present\n| employer           = \n| organization       = [[David Horowitz Freedom Center]]\n| agent              = \n| known_for          = [[Islamophobia|Anti-Muslim views]], <br />books and websites about <br />[[Jihad]] and [[Islamic terrorism]]\n| notable_works      = ''[[The Truth About Muhammad|The Truth About Muhammad: Founder of the World's Most Intolerant Religion]]'', (2006)<br />''[[The Politically Incorrect Guide to Islam (And the Crusades)]]'', (2005)\n| influences         = \n| influenced         = \n| home_town          = \n| salary             = \n| net_worth          = \n| television         = \n| party              = \n| movement           = \n| boards             = \n| religion           = \n| spouse             = \n| parents            = \n| relatives          = \n| awards             = \n| website            = {{URL|jihadwatch.org}}\n| footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Robert Bruce Spencer''' is an American anti-Muslim<ref name=\"Anti-Muslim-speakers-Washingtonpost\"/><ref name=\"Isaacs-Unz-American-Islamophobia\">{{cite web |last1=Isaacs |first1=Arnold |title=American Islamophobia's Fake Facts |url=http://www.unz.com/tengelhardt/american-islamophobias-fake-facts/ |website=The Unz Review |accessdate=July 13, 2019 |date=July 31, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Ernst-book-Islamophobia-in-America\">{{Cite book|url=https://www.palgrave.com/gp/book/9781137290069|title=Islamophobia in America - The Anatomy of Intolerance {{!}} C. Ernst {{!}} Palgrave Macmillan|last=|first=|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=4, 125-126, 163|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"BBC-US-bloggers-banned-from-UK\"/> author and [[blogger]]. Spencer describes himself as \"the 'good' kind of [[Islamophobia|Islamophobe]]\".<ref name=\"case-for-islamophobia-Spencer-frontpagemag\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.frontpagemag.com/fpm/268634/case-islamophobia-robert-spencer|title=The Case for Islamophobia|date=December 6, 2017|work=Frontpage Mag|access-date=May 23, 2018}}</ref> His published books include two [[New York Times Best Seller list|''New York Times'' bestsellers]].\n\nIn 2003 he founded and has since directed  [[Islamophobia|Islamophobe]] blog [[Jihad Watch]], . He co-founded the anti-Muslim group [[Stop Islamization of America]] (American Freedom Defense Initiative) with blogger [[Pamela Geller]].<ref name=\"KaplanL\u00f6\u00f6w2017\">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mxE4DwAAQBAJ&pg=PT214|title=Lone Wolf and Autonomous Cell Terrorism|author1=Jeffrey Kaplan|author2=Hel\u00e9ne L\u00f6\u00f6w|author3=Leena Malkki|publisher=Taylor & Francis|year=2017|isbn=978-1-317-53042-8|page=214}}</ref> Reports that two of Spencer's books were listed in [[FBI]] training materials and that he had given seminars to various law enforcement units in the United States stirred controversy.<ref name=\"Anti-Muslim-speakers-Washingtonpost\">{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/religion/anti-muslim-speakers-still-popular-in-law-enforcement-training/2014/03/12/bc8d8e30-aa1c-11e3-8a7b-c1c684e2671f_story.html|title=Anti-Muslim speakers still popular in law enforcement training|date=March 12, 2014|work=[[The Washington Post]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170318114828/https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/religion/anti-muslim-speakers-still-popular-in-law-enforcement-training/2014/03/12/bc8d8e30-aa1c-11e3-8a7b-c1c684e2671f_story.html|archive-date=March 18, 2017|url-status=live|access-date=September 10, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" /> He has frequently appeared on [[Fox News]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mediamatters.org/blog/2015/01/13/meet-the-extremists-who-lead-foxs-conversation/202119|title=Meet The Extremists Who Lead Fox's Conversation About Islam|date=January 13, 2015|work=[[Media Matters]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170211080539/https://mediamatters.org/blog/2015/01/13/meet-the-extremists-who-lead-foxs-conversation/202119|archive-date=February 11, 2017|url-status=live|access-date=February 10, 2017}}</ref>  In 2013 the [[UK Home Office]] barred Spencer from travel to the [[UK]] for 3 to 5 years for \"making [[#uk ban statement|statements]]  that may foster hatred that might lead to inter-community violence\".\n\n==Background==\nSpencer was baptized in the [[Greek Orthodox Church]] and joined the [[Melkite Greek Catholic Church]] in 1984.<ref name=\"Spencer bio\">{{cite web|url=http://www.jihadwatch.org/about-robert-spencer.html|title=About Robert Spencer|publisher=Jihad Watch|accessdate=October 29, 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101229102419/http://www.jihadwatch.org/about-robert-spencer.html|archivedate=December 29, 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"Spero News\">{{cite news|url=http://www.speroforum.com/a/42470/Pope-must-condemn-demonizing-of-Israel|title=Pope must condemn demonizing of Israel|last=Spencer|first=Robert|date=October 26, 2010|work=Spero News|access-date=October 29, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101029001117/http://www.speroforum.com/a/42470/Pope-must-condemn-demonizing-of-Israel|archive-date=October 29, 2010|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":3\" /> In a 2006 interview, Spencer stated that his grandparents were forced to emigrate from an area that is now part of Turkey because they were [[Christianity|Christians]].<ref name=\"lamb\">{{cite web|url=http://www.c-span.org/video/?193778-1/qa-robert-spencer|date=August 20, 2006|title=Robert Spencer Jihad Watch, Director Q & A with Brian Lamb|publisher=CSpan|accessdate=November 30, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141109043825/http://www.c-span.org/video/?193778-1%2Fqa-robert-spencer|archive-date=November 9, 2014|url-status=live}}</ref> According to a 2010 interview in ''[[New York (magazine)|New York]]'' magazine, Spencer's father worked for the [[Voice of America]] during the [[Cold War]], and in his younger days, Spencer himself worked at Revolution Books, a [[Maoist]] bookstore in [[New York City]] founded by [[Robert Avakian]].<ref name=\"Muhammad comes to\">{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/news/features/67635/index2.html|title=Muhammad Comes to Manhattan|work=New York|author=Mark Jacobson|date=August 22, 2010|accessdate=November 1, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100826065300/http://nymag.com/news/features/67635/index2.html|archive-date=August 26, 2010|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nSpencer received an M.A. in 1986 in [[religious studies]] from the [[University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill]]. His masters thesis was on Catholic history.<ref name=UNC>{{cite web|url=http://webcat.lib.unc.edu/record=b2172870~S1|publisher=UNC-CH Libraries|work=Davis Library Thesis, Religion, 1986|title=The monophysite in the mirror, by Robert Bruce Spencer|access-date=March 20, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170301144945/http://webcat.lib.unc.edu/record=b2172870~S1|archive-date=March 1, 2017|url-status=live|year=1986}}</ref> He has said he has been studying Islamic theology, law, and history since 1980.<ref name=\"lamb\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://trib.com/news/local/article_2428fa7c-c843-561b-80ac-b243218b92be.html |title=Marines gather to honor, celebrate |publisher=Trib.com |date=October 26, 2005 |accessdate=November 1, 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170908021137/http://trib.com/news/local/article_2428fa7c-c843-561b-80ac-b243218b92be.html |archive-date=September 8, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> He worked in [[think tank]]s for more than 20 years,<ref name=\"Muhammad comes to\"/> and in 2002\u20132003 was an adjunct fellow with the [[Free Congress Research and Education Foundation|Free Congress Foundation]].<ref name=\"tribute\">{{cite web|url=http://www.catholic.org/national/national_story.php?id=31171|title=A Tribute: Paul Weyrich Has Died|date=December 19, 2008|accessdate=December 16, 2010|author=Robert Spencer|publisher=Catholic Online|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090309161405/http://www.catholic.org/national/national_story.php?id=31171|archivedate=March 9, 2009}}</ref> Spencer named [[Paul Weyrich]], also a Melkite Catholic, as a mentor of his writings on Islam. Spencer writes, \"Paul Weyrich taught me a great deal, by word and by example&nbsp;\u2013 about how to deal both personally and professionally with the slanders and smears that are a daily aspect of this work.\"<ref name=\"tribute\"/>\n\nCriticized by clergy in the Catholic Church because of his views on Islam, Spencer left the church in 2016 to return to the [[Greek Orthodox Church]].<ref name=\":3\">{{cite web|url=https://www.crisismagazine.com/2018/robert-spencer-and-the-religion-of-terror|title=Robert Spencer and the Religion of Terror|work=Crisis Magazine|author=Jeffrey Rubin|date=October 25, 2018|accessdate=October 26, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181025120653/https://www.crisismagazine.com/2018/robert-spencer-and-the-religion-of-terror|archive-date=October 25, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Views on Islam==\nSpencer is known for his anti-Muslim views.<ref name=\"Anti-Muslim-speakers-Washingtonpost\"/><ref name=\"Isaacs-Unz-American-Islamophobia\"/><ref name=\"Ernst-book-Islamophobia-in-America\"/><ref name=\"BBC-US-bloggers-banned-from-UK\"/><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomsbury.com/uk/right-wing-populism-in-europe-9781780932453/|title=Right-Wing Populism in Europe|website=Bloomsbury Publishing|pages=90\u201392|language=en|access-date=July 12, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/08/04/us/04extreme.html|title=To Fight Radical Islam, U.S. Wants Muslim Allies|last=Shane|first=Scott|date=August 3, 2011|work=The New York Times|access-date=April 21, 2019|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.desmoinesregister.com/story/news/politics/2017/01/29/iowas-congressional-delegation-responds-trump-immigration-order/97221888/|title=Iowa's congressional delegation responds to Trump immigration order|website=Des Moines Register|language=en|access-date=July 12, 2019}}</ref> Spencer describes himself a [[Islamophobe]] of \"Good kind\" ,<ref name=\"case-for-islamophobia-Spencer-frontpagemag\"/> and is a commentator on [[radical Islam]].<ref name=\"Deland 2014 p. 162\">{{cite book|title=In the Tracks of Breivik: Far Right Networks in Northern and Eastern Europe|last=Deland|first=Mats|publisher=Lit Verlag|year=2014|isbn=978-3-643-90542-0|location=Berlin Wien|page=162}}</ref>\n\nSpencer co-founded the anti-Muslim<ref name=\"Anti-Muslim-speakers-Washingtonpost\"/><ref name=\"Isaacs-Unz-American-Islamophobia\"/><ref name=\"Ernst-book-Islamophobia-in-America\"/><ref name=\"BBC-US-bloggers-banned-from-UK\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-23064355|title=US bloggers banned from entering UK|date=June 26, 2013|access-date=July 11, 2019|language=en-GB}}</ref> group [[Stop Islamization of America]] (also known as the [[American Freedom Defense Initiative]]) with [[Pamela Geller]] in 2010. The organization is designated as a [[hate group]] by the [[Anti-Defamation League]]<ref>[http://www.adl.org/main_Extremism/sioa.htm \"Backgrounder: Stop Islamization of America (SIOA)\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120502054200/http://www.adl.org/main_Extremism/sioa.htm |date=May 2, 2012 }}. ''Extremism''. [[Anti-Defamation League]]. March 25, 2011 [August 26, 2010]. Retrieved February 16, 2012.</ref> and the [[Southern Poverty Law Center]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Lach, Eric|date=March 1, 2011|work=[[Talking Points Memo]]|url=http://tpmmuckraker.talkingpointsmemo.com/2011/03/pam_geller_on_splc_hate_group_label_badge_of_honor.php|title=Pam Geller On 'Hate Group' Label: 'A Badge of Honor'|access-date=February 17, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120313082234/http://tpmmuckraker.talkingpointsmemo.com/2011/03/pam_geller_on_splc_hate_group_label_badge_of_honor.php|archive-date=March 13, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Pamela Geller & Stop Islamization of America|url=http://www.splcenter.org/get-informed/intelligence-files/profiles/pamela-geller|publisher=Southern Poverty Law Center|accessdate=June 27, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110625194540/http://www.splcenter.org/get-informed/intelligence-files/profiles/pamela-geller|archive-date=June 25, 2011|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Steinback|first=Robert|title=Jihad Against Islam|url=http://www.splcenter.org/get-informed/intelligence-report/browse-all-issues/2011/summer/jihad-against-islam|work=Intelligence Report, Issue #142|publisher=Southern Poverty Law Center|accessdate=June 27, 2011|date=Summer 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120119075935/http://www.splcenter.org/get-informed/intelligence-report/browse-all-issues/2011/summer/jihad-against-islam|archive-date=January 19, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> Along with Geller, he led a campaign to stop the building of Park51, an Islamic community center near the World Trade Center, which they referred to as the \"Ground Zero Mosque\".<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn 2009, Spencer said Obama was to blame for false rumors that he was a \"secret Muslim\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/06/03/muslim-again/|title=Muslim Again?|last=Etheridge|first=Eric|date=June 3, 2009|website=Opinionator|language=en-US|access-date=July 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2011, ''[[Wired (Magazine)|Wired]]'' reported that two of Spencer's books were listed in [[FBI]] training materials. Both ''[[The Truth About Muhammad]]'' and ''[[The Politically Incorrect Guide to Islam]]'' were recommended for agents hoping to better understand Islam.<ref name=\":1\">{{cite journal|author=Ackerman, Spencer|date=July 27, 2011|journal=[[Wired (Magazine)|Wired]]|url=https://www.wired.com/2011/07/fbi-islam-101-guide/|title=FBI 'Islam 101' Guide Depicted Muslims as 7th-Century Simpletons|access-date=November 21, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181204011823/https://www.wired.com/2011/07/fbi-islam-101-guide/|archive-date=December 4, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Anders Behring Breivik|Anders Breivik]], the Norwegian spree killer behind the [[2011 Norway attacks|2011 Norway terrorist attacks]] which killed 77, cited Spencer 64 times in his manifesto and wrote of him, \"About Islam I recommend essentially everything written by Robert Spencer.\"<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Gardell|first=Mattias|date=January 1, 2014|title=Crusader Dreams: Oslo 22/7, Islamophobia, and the Quest for a Monocultural Europe|journal=Terrorism and Political Violence|volume=26|issue=1|pages=129\u2013155|doi=10.1080/09546553.2014.849930|issn=0954-6553}}</ref> Spencer condemned Breivik and said he was unfairly blamed by the media for the attack.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/25/us/25debate.html|title=Killings in Norway Spotlight Anti-Muslim Thought in U.S.|last=Shane|first=Scott|date=July 24, 2011|work=The New York Times|access-date=July 12, 2019|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref name=\":2\" />\n\n==Controversies==\nThe government of Pakistan banned Spencer's book, ''[[The Truth About Muhammad]]'', in 2016, citing \"objectionable material\" as the cause.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.nationalreview.com/phi-beta-cons/45068/pakistan-book-closed-muhammad-candace-de-russy |title= Pakistan: Book Closed on Muhammad |access-date= April 19, 2015 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150612204845/http://www.nationalreview.com/phi-beta-cons/45068/pakistan-book-closed-muhammad-candace-de-russy |archive-date= June 12, 2015 |url-status= live |date= January 9, 2007 }}</ref> ''[[Onward Muslim Soldiers]]'' was banned in Malaysia in 2007.<ref name=\"BERNAMA\">{{cite news|title=Ministry Bans 14 Books|url=http://www.bernama.com.my/bernama/v3/printable.php?id=272915|newspaper=[[BERNAMA]]|date=July 12, 2007|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303221210/http://www.bernama.com.my/bernama/v3/printable.php?id=272915|archivedate=March 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn an October 2010 news article, an investigative report by ''[[The Tennessean]]'' described Spencer as one of several individuals who \"... cash in on spreading hate and fear about Islam.\" ''Tennessean'' investigation concluded: \"IRS filings from 2008 show that Robert Spencer earned $132,537 from the [[David Horowitz Freedom Center]], and Horowitz pocketed over $400,000 for himself in just one year.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tennessean.com/article/20101024/NEWS01/10240374/Anti-Muslim-crusaders-make-millions-spreading-fear|title=Anti-Muslim crusaders make millions spreading fear|date=October 24, 2010|accessdate=November 4, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tennessean.com/assets/pdf/DN1658821023.PDF|title=David Horowitz Freedom Center's IRS Form 990|date=June 3, 2009|accessdate=April 24, 2011}}</ref>\n\nOn April 13, 2017, Spencer spoke at the [[Truman State University]] despite protests and a petition against him. He was invited by the [[Young America's Foundation]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/education/truman-state-grapples-with-controversial-anti-muslim-speaker/article_138f0acd-bd84-59e1-890e-d921a1ec6ee2.html|title=Truman State grapples with controversial anti-Muslim speaker|publisher=St. Louis Post-Dispatch|access-date=May 3, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424121832/http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/education/truman-state-grapples-with-controversial-anti-muslim-speaker/article_138f0acd-bd84-59e1-890e-d921a1ec6ee2.html|archive-date=April 24, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On May 1, 2017, Spencer spoke at the [[University of Buffalo]]. There he was shouted down and heckled.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://buffalonews.com/2017/05/01/controversial-speaker-ub-shouted-heckled/|title=No violence, but UB speaker greeted with tension, heckling|publisher=The Buffalo News|access-date=May 3, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170502134727/http://buffalonews.com/2017/05/01/controversial-speaker-ub-shouted-heckled/|archive-date=May 2, 2017|url-status=live|date=May 2, 2017}}</ref> On May 3, 2017, Spencer spoke at [[Gettysburg College]]; 375 alumni urged the college president [[Janet Morgan Riggs]] to cancel the speech, but the event went on as planned.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://gettysburgian.com/2017/05/open-letter-from-375-alums-urges-president-riggs-to-cancel-robert-spencers-speech/|title=Open letter from 375 alums urges President Riggs to cancel Robert Spencer's speech|date=May 1, 2017|newspaper=[[The Gettysburgian]]|access-date=May 3, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170503155217/http://gettysburgian.com/2017/05/open-letter-from-375-alums-urges-president-riggs-to-cancel-robert-spencers-speech/|archive-date=May 3, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Spencer said, \"There is one kind of diversity that is not valued generally in an academic setting and that is intellectual diversity.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://gettysburgian.com/2017/05/robert-spencers-speech-at-gettysburg-college-engages-students-in-civil-discourse/|title=Robert Spencer's speech at Gettysburg College engages students in civil discourse|author=Pontz, Benjamin|date=May 3, 2017|newspaper=The Gettysburgian|access-date=May 4, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170504173030/http://gettysburgian.com/2017/05/robert-spencers-speech-at-gettysburg-college-engages-students-in-civil-discourse/|archive-date=May 4, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On November 14, 2017, Spencer spoke at [[Stanford University]]. Many students walked out during the event.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcbayarea.com/news/local/Stanford-Students-Walk-Out-Protest-During-Robert-Spencer-Speaking-Event-457635203.html|title=Stanford Students Walk Out, Protest During Robert Spencer Speaking Event|publisher=NBC Bay Area|access-date=November 16, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171117001808/https://www.nbcbayarea.com/news/local/Stanford-Students-Walk-Out-Protest-During-Robert-Spencer-Speaking-Event-457635203.html|archive-date=November 17, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nSpencer said that \"a young Icelandic Leftist\" poisoned him in 2017 in Reykjavik, Iceland.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://icelandmag.is/article/controversial-us-author-robert-spencer-claims-he-was-poisoned-leftist-while-iceland |title = Controversial US author Robert Spencer claims he was poisoned by \"leftist\" while in Iceland}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://grapevine.is/news/2017/05/16/islamophobe-robert-spencer-claims-young-leftist-poisoned-him/ |title = Islamophobe Robert Spencer Claims Young Leftist Poisoned Him|date = May 16, 2017}}</ref> Spencer also criticized the doctor who then treated him and the police who investigated.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://archives.frontpagemag.com/fpm/leftist-privilege-poisoned-iceland-year-ago-no-one-robert-spencer/ |title =Leftist Privilege: Poisoned in Iceland a year ago, no one arrested |publisher=[[Frontpagemag]] |date=May 21, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Ban from entering the UK===\nOn June 26, 2013, Spencer and [[Pamela Geller]] were banned from entering the UK.<ref>{{cite news|title=US bloggers banned from entering UK|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-23064355|accessdate=June 27, 2013|publisher=BBC|date=June 26, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130627011447/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-23064355|archive-date=June 27, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> They were due to speak at an [[English Defence League]] march in [[Woolwich]], south London, where Drummer [[Murder of Lee Rigby|Lee Rigby]] was killed. [[Home Secretary]] [[Theresa May]] informed Spencer and Geller that their presence in the UK would \"not be conducive to the public good\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Rawlinson|first=Kevin|title=Anti-Ground Zero Mosque campaigners Pamela Geller and Robert Spencer barred from entering Britain to speak at an EDL rally|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/antiground-zero-mosque-campaigners-pamela-geller-and-robert-spencer-barred-from-entering-britain-to-speak-at-an-edl-rally-8675251.html|accessdate=June 27, 2013|newspaper=The Independent|date=June 26, 2013|location=London|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130627192049/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/antiground-zero-mosque-campaigners-pamela-geller-and-robert-spencer-barred-from-entering-britain-to-speak-at-an-edl-rally-8675251.html|archive-date=June 27, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nA letter from the UK Home Office stated that this decision is based on Spencer's statement that: \"It [Islam] is a religion or a belief system that mandates warfare against unbelievers for the purpose of establishing a societal model that is absolutely incompatible with Western society. ...Because of media and general government unwillingness to face the sources of Islamic terrorism these things remain largely unknown.\"<ref>{{cite video|title=The Speech that Got Robert Spencer Banned From the UK|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=June 27, 2013|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rHdUgc6gxDI|access-date=December 1, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202053606/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rhdugc6gxdi|archive-date=February 2, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe decision<!-- \", which they cannot appeal,\"-it was appealed in 2015-see below--> will stand for between three and five years. The ban followed a concerted campaign by the UK anti-racism organization [[Hope not Hate]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Anti-Muslim pair banned from UK|url=http://www.express.co.uk/news/uk/410494/Anti-Muslim-pair-banned-from-UK|accessdate=June 27, 2013|newspaper=Daily Express|location=UK|date=June 26, 2013}}</ref> which said it had collected 26,000 signatures for a petition to the Home Secretary.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lowles|first=Nick|title=Geller and Spencer Banned|url=http://www.hopenothate.org.uk/blog/article/2803/geller-and-spencer-banned|publisher=Hope not Hate|accessdate=June 27, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130630023715/http://www.hopenothate.org.uk/blog/article/2803/geller-and-spencer-banned|archive-date=June 30, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> Spencer and Geller contested the ban, but in 2015 the [[British Court of Appeals]] dismissed the appeal, arguing  that \"this was a public order case where the police had advised that significant public disorder and serious violence might ensue from the proposed visit.\"<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bailii.org/cgi-bin/markup.cgi?doc=/ew/cases/EWCA/Civ/2015/45.html&query=geller&method=boolean | title=Geller & Anor, R (on the application of) v The Secretary of State for the Home Department [2015] EWCA Civ 45 (05 February 2015) | publisher=[[British and Irish Legal Information Institute]] | accessdate=October 31, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"UK Human Rights Blog\">{{cite web | url=https://ukhumanrightsblog.com/2015/02/15/critics-of-islam-prevented-from-entering-uk-to-attend-lee-rigby-rally/ | title=Critics of Islam prevented from entering UK to attend Lee Rigby rally | publisher=1 Crown Office Row | work=UK Human Rights Blog | date=February 15, 2015 | accessdate=October 31, 2017 | author=English, Rosalind}}</ref>\n\nThe ban was criticised by [[Douglas Murray (author)|Douglas Murray]]. He stated that Islamist hate preachers are still allowed to enter the UK.<ref>{{cite news|title=A gross double standard over hate speech|url=http://blogs.spectator.co.uk/2013/06/a-gross-double-standard-over-hate-speech/|accessdate=February 8, 2017|newspaper=[[The Spectator]]|location=UK|date=June 27, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114143645/http://blogs.spectator.co.uk/2013/06/a-gross-double-standard-over-hate-speech/|archive-date=November 14, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n\n===Best sellers===\n* ''[[The Truth About Muhammad: Founder of the World's Most Intolerant Religion]]'', [[Regnery Publishing|Regnery Press]], 2006 ([[New York Times|NYT]] bestseller list \u2013 2006-10-29<ref name=autogenerated1>[https://www.nytimes.com/2006/10/29/books/bestseller/1029besthardnonfiction.html?ex=1168923600&en=acb5c34abdb92f18&ei=5070 Best Sellers \u2013 Hardcover Nonfiction] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402190205/http://www.nytimes.com/2006/10/29/books/bestseller/1029besthardnonfiction.html?ex=1168923600&en=acb5c34abdb92f18&ei=5070 |date=April 2, 2015 }} \u2013 [[NYT]]</ref>) {{ISBN|1-59698-028-1}} {{OCLC|232648493}}\n* ''[[The Politically Incorrect Guide to Islam (And the Crusades)]]'', Regnery Press, 2005. (NYT bestseller list \u2013 2005-10-16<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2005/10/16/books/bestseller/1016bestpapernonfiction.html?ex=1168923600&en=f4feabaad368de1c&ei=5070 Paperback Nonfiction] \u2013 [[NYT]]</ref>) {{ISBN|0-89526-013-1}} {{OCLC|779057129}}\n\n===Other books===\n*{{cite book|title=Palestinian Delusion: The Catastrophic History of the Middle East Peace Process|publisher=Bombardier Book|date=December 3, 2019|isbn=978-1642932546|oclc=}}\n* {{cite book|title=The History of Jihad: From Muhammad to ISIS|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1682616606|publisher=Bombardier Books|date=August 7, 2018|isbn=9781682616598|oclc=1046676281}}\n* {{cite book|title=Confessions of an Islamophobe|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1682614913|publisher=Bombardier Books|date=November 28, 2017|isbn=978-1682614914|oclc=1022710774}}\n* {{cite book|title=Not Peace But a Sword: The Great Chasm Between Christianity and Islam|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1938983289|publisher=Catholic Answers|date=March 25, 2013|isbn=978-1938983283|oclc=840646024}}\n* {{cite book|title=The Post-American Presidency: The Obama Administration's War on America|author=Pamela Geller|author2=Robert Spencer |publisher=Threshold Editions|date=July 27, 2010|isbn=978-1-4391-8930-6|title-link=The Post-American Presidency: The Obama Administration's War on America}}\n* {{cite book|title=The Complete Infidel's Guide to Free Speech (and Its Enemies)|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1621576515|publisher= Regnery Press|date=July 24, 2017|page=256|isbn=978-1621576273|oclc=993696636}}\n* {{cite book|title=The Complete Infidels' Guide to Iran|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1621575306|publisher= Regnery Press|date=July 11, 2016|page=256|isbn=978-1621575160|oclc= \t952247204}}\n* {{cite book|title=The Complete Infidel's Guide to ISIS|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1621574644|publisher= Regnery Press|date=August 24, 2015|page=|isbn=978-1-62157-453-8|oclc= \t916923210}}\n* {{cite book|title=The Complete Infidels' Guide to the Koran|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1596981261|publisher= Regnery Press|date=September 21, 2009|page=260|isbn=978-1-59698-104-1|oclc=317454159}}\n** downloadable version<ref>{{cite web|url=https://issuu.com/guraja/docs/spencer__robert_-_the_complete_infi  |title=The Complete Infidels Guide to the Koran  |author=Spencer, Robert|date=September 21, 2009|work=[[Simon & Schuster]] |accessdate=March 9, 2020}}</ref>\n* {{cite book|title=Did Muhammad Exist?: An Inquiry Into Islam's Obscure Origins|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1497608562|publisher=ISI Books|date=March 2012|isbn=978-1-61017-061-1|oclc=883649585}}\n* {{cite book|title=Stealth Jihad: How Radical Islam is Subverting America without Guns or Bombs|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1596980753|publisher=Regnery Press|date=October 28, 2008|isbn=978-1-59698-556-8|oclc=740862521}}\n* {{cite book|title=Religion of Peace?: Why Christianity Is and Islam Isn't|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1596985356|publisher=Regnery Publishing|year=2007|page=|isbn=978-1-59698-515-5|oclc=929251820}}\n* ''[[The Myth of Islamic Tolerance|The Myth of Islamic Tolerance: How Islamic Law Treats Non-Muslims]]'' (editor), [[Prometheus Books]], 2005. {{ISBN|1-59102-249-5}} {{OCLC|551266709}}\n* ''[[Onward Muslim Soldiers|Onward Muslim Soldiers: How Jihad Still Threatens America and the West]]'', [[Regnery Publishing]], 2003. {{ISBN|0-89526-100-6}} {{OCLC|892799748}}\n* {{cite book|title=Inside Islam: A Guide for Catholics: 100 questions and answers|url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=0965922855|publisher=Ascension Press|year=2003|page=197|isbn=978-0-9659228-5-2}}\n* {{cite book|title=Islam Unveiled: Disturbing Questions About the World's Fastest Growing Faith|url=https://archive.org/details/islamunveileddis00robe|url-access=registration|publisher=Encounter Books|date=October 25, 2002|page=[https://archive.org/details/islamunveileddis00robe/page/202 202]|isbn=978-1-893554-58-0|oclc=752326911}}\n** downloadable version<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=eanFm7hiM1cC&q=page+75#v=onepage&q=page%2075&f=false  |title=Islam Unveiled: Disturbing Questions about the World's Fastest-Growing Faith |author=Spencer, Robert|date=October 25, 2002|work=[[Encounter Books]]|accessdate=March 9, 2020|isbn=9781594032950 }}</ref>\n* {{cite book|title=The Arab Winter Comes to America: The Truth about the War We're In|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=S2pLngEACAAJ|date=April 14, 2014|publisher=Regnery Publishing, Incorporated, An Eagle Publishing Company|isbn=978-1-62157-204-6|oclc=877883931}}\n\n===Pamphlets===\n\n*{{Citation\n| last       = \n| first      =\n| year       = 2013\n| title      = Islam: Religion of Bigots\n| publisher  = The David Horowitz Freedom Center\n| location =\n| page       = 20\n| url        = http://www.frontpagemag.com/sites/default/files/uploads/2013/10/religionofbigots.pdf\n| asin       = B00EYQZS9Y\n}}\n*{{Citation\n| last       = \n| first      =\n| year       = 2011\n| title      = Islamophobia: Thought Crime of the Totalitarian Future\n| publisher  = The David Horowitz Freedom Center\n| location =\n| page       = 56\n| url        =\n| asin       = B005R3336I\n}}\n*{{Citation\n| last       = \n| first      =\n| year       = 2011\n| title      = Muslim Persecution of Christians\n| publisher  = The David Horowitz Freedom Center\n| location =\n| page       = 40\n| url        =\n| asin       = B0058P4PHG\n}}\n*{{Citation\n| last       = \n| first      =\n| year       = 2012\n| title      = Muslim Brotherhood in America\n| publisher  = The David Horowitz Freedom Center\n| location =\n| page       = 28\n| url        = http://www.frontpagemag.com/sites/default/files/uploads/2011/03/mbia.pdf\n| asin       = B007GEJD92\n}}\n*{{Citation\n| last       = \n| first      =\n| year       = 2007\n| title      = What Americans Need to Know About Jihad\n| publisher  = The David Horowitz Freedom Center\n| location =\n| page       = 15\n| url        = http://www.frontpagemag.com/sites/default/files/uploads/2011/03/jihad.pdf\n| asin       = B0058PIX74\n}}\n\n===Interviews===\n*{{YouTube|HcEUz0gPaUE|The Glenn Beck Podcast Ep. 2}} by [[Glenn Beck]]\n*{{YouTube|sma4WYRuTXY|Bill O'Reilly's Interview with Robert Spencer}} by [[Bill O'Reilly (political commentator)|Bill O'Reilly]]\n*[http://www1.cbn.com/content/robert-spencer-politically-incorrect-guide-islam Pat Robertson interview] by [[Pat Robertson]]\n*{{YouTube|D7zpH4xt5rA|THE SAAD TRUTH_174}} by [[Gad Saad]]\n*{{YouTube|qvjeRFQvbrY|Confessions of An Islamophobe}}\n\n==See also==\n{{Wikipedia books\n |1=Robert Spencer\n}}\n{{Portal|Islam|Freedom of speech}}\n* [[List of books banned by governments]]\n* [[A Common Word Between Us and You]]\n* [[Catholic\u2013Muslim Forum]]\n* ''[[Islam: What the West Needs to Know]]''\n* [[John Paul II Center for Interreligious Dialogue]]\n* [[Pontifical Council for Interreligious Dialogue]]\n* [[Bibliography of books critical of Islam]]\n* [http://www.worldcat.org/identities/lccn-n2002-104117/ WorldCat author entry for 'Spencer, Robert 1962-']\n\